Happy December 1st from the Million Dollar Listing Panel!!! ❤️✨❄️

My to do list usually follows this general theme: wake up, breathe, drink some water, move, and get to work! 

I try not to take myself so seriously, REMIND myself that it’s inevitable that im going to fail and to have fun.  We all failed when we took our first steps as babies, didn’t we?  Not only was it celebrated, but I’m pretty sure it was also kinda cute?  Go accumulate a few funny failures this week and report back and if anything use them to keep you humble. 

Let’s talk about mindset: To each their own however there’s no complaining or negativity coming out of me because there’s just NEVER NOT going to be something to complain about or be negative about… so you might as well let other people jump on that complain train because trust me, you don’t want to end up where that trains going and trust me again, if you don’t complain, don’t worry, someone else will. So just don’t take that class ! 

Waking up happier is also choice and the more consistently you make that choice, it’ll become a habit and if you’re happy, you’re ultimately living a happy life right now, aren’t you? Regardless of what’s happening around you, if you decide to wake up happy, I won’t be able to stop you from do something fun like chasing your dreams (and then writing long run on sentences about it like me). 

Always remember how far you’ve come… who helped you along the way, and yes, ‘luck’ does happen when work meets opportunity! 

Lastly, leaving this room super inspired today by my colleagues to be and do even more! 

Thanks KWREA family for having me this afternoon and thank you to the goat, Stephen Hanlon @triguy1117 for hosting us. 🙏🏽✨

Cheers to a great December 🎅 🥂

Still looking? Get a Town or a Village Home in Milton from a trusted home builder today. There are many out there, so choose wisely. 🏠🏘️✨🫶🏽

This is why you need to pay attention to builders: The average building is about $300M. Half of that is carried as debt which is fine. Many friends have called asking me to inquire what’s happening with their building, why construction hasn’t started yet despite deposits being paid. Why are builders stalling? For starters, on top of the debt, for each 1% increase in interest rates, it equates to 1.5M a year. Over 4 years that’s 6M. Well, when the interest goes up 4%, that’s a whopping $24Million. 

This means that if a developer is not well capitalized. You are in danger! 

Also, the Atwal Realty Group Meets Mattamy Homes… sega continues! Love when my commercial/acting career crosses over with real estate! 

In my opinion, one of the best ways to wind down at the end of a long day is by enjoying a delicious meal in the comfort of your own home, with your significant others #bliss. (Disclaimer: the wonderful Miss. Lindura is just my onscreen boo 😅). 

Give me a call to discuss 🏡 📱

The homes features include upgraded LED light fixtures and dimmers throughout, upgraded kitchen single basin sink and tall neck faucet with pull down sprayer, incognito Miele dishwasher, custom built-in units in living room, upgraded pantry and laundry storage, crown moulding throughout, custom walk in built in closets, gas line for BBQ on the massive Terrace! 

Working with first time home buyers is such a unique and special experience, and I'm thrilled to have been a part of introducing them to the world of real estate. We've shared plenty of laughs along the way, and I couldn't be happier for this amazing accomplishment. Here's to your beautiful new home, and all the joy and happiness it will bring! Congratulations again, you two rockstars!

1. Your worth is inherent, not earned. Kobe’s father said something along these lines to him when he scored 0 points during a summer league at age 13.  That’s a game changer. You don’t need to be something to be any more loved. 

2. Your value transcends achievements. It’s great to achieve but you matter simply because you exist!  Celebrate the external accomplishments but be careful that you don’t let them validate you as a human. 

3. Your presence alone is a gift. Your weirdness, personality, uniqueness contribute to the tapestry of humanity. If people don’t see it, it doesn’t make it any less real. 

4. Self-worth comes from self acceptance. Embrace the thoughts you have, the ‘flaws’ and ‘imperfections’ for that is what makes you so much more powerful! 

5. Love matters the most. Kindness is the key. Be a beacon of hope for someone and help them see that they are more than their productivity and accomplishments. 

Lastly, once we embrace truths about who we are, we start walking knowing we are all masterpieces in progress.  Key word, we are already masterpieces. The journey is the unfolding of that masterpiece.  Things, our thoughts and beliefs and people will either help us unlock and unleash the potential or hinder us from unleashing that greatness. 

Embrace the sacredness within you and let your light shine, for in Gods eyes, you are fearfully and wonderfully made. Say it out loud and let that permeate within you’re entire being every cell and fibre. Amen. 

#unleash #jinderatwal #greatness #truth #sacred

🔑 Unlocking Success: My Personal Journey from Rookie to Six-Figure Earner in Less Than 6 Months! 💼💰 #6months 

🎙️ Speaking to this intimate audience about my journey to becoming a six-figure income earner in less than 12 months and the powerful impact cultivating an environment of serving others. 🙌

When I first dove into the world of real estate, my main aim was to make a positive impact and help people achieve their wildest dreams. Today I'm overflowing with gratitude as I share that through sheer dedication, unwavering determination, and an unshakeable passion for serving my clients, I've transformed my rookie status to raking in a six-figure income. 📈

But this journey isn't just about the numbers which I hope my clients would testify to; it's about the stories of incredible individuals & families I've had the privilege to assist along the way. It’s more than mere transactions; it's about building genuine connections, turning dreams into reality, and leaving a lasting impact on people's lives. 🏡💚

As someone who cherishes the connections we've built in this space, I'm wholeheartedly committed to sharing practical tips, valuable insights, inspiring content to empower you on your own real estate or business journey. Most of you already know that despite being based in Toronto, I've spent countless hours helping friends trade real estate in different provinces like my home province, beautiful British Columbia, without expecting anything in return. That's when I knew I had found my calling—making a difference wherever I can. Together, let's uncover the secrets of success, uplifting and supporting one another. 🌟🤝

Thanks for all of you who have joined me on this incredible adventure by following my page @jinderatwalrealtor. 

Remember, greatness is never achieved alone—it's a result of collective effort. So, don't forget to tag a friend who could use a dose of real estate inspiration, and let's build an extraordinary community of achievers! 🌍🙏

🔥 Rebound Your Way to a Healthy Mind and Body! 🔥
Hey there, ya health-conscious folks!  So, I recently discovered this… and then realized along with the feeling like a kid again, it has a whole laundry list of benefits… 

In a peer reviewed study with sedentary rural folks with type 2 diabetes, half did rebound exercise while the other half others didn’t. The rebound group had big improvements in HbA1c, FPG, and BMI. Oh and nothing bad happened… here’s more of the benefits! 

💡 Mind Boost:
* Gain a sense of control and improve self image. 
* Sharpen your mental performance and learning processes.
* Improve coordination and responsiveness of your muscle fibers.
* Enhance balance and keep your brain on its toes (reduce anxiety and depressive episodes). 

🏋️ Body Bliss:
* Get that lymphatic system flowing and feel refreshed!
* Kiss high blood pressure goodbye during exertion.
* Boost digestion and elimination for a happy tummy.
* Supercharge blood circulation and bring those nutrients to your cells.
* Protect your joints from chronic fatigue and impact.
* Promote tissue repair and be a self-healing superstar.
* Breathe easier and increase your lung capacity.
* Fire up your metabolism and burn calories even after you’re done.
* Lower cholesterol and triglycerides levels for a happier heart.
* Wave goodbye to chronic edema and swelling.
* Supercharge your musculoskeletal system with increased G-force.
* Get that oxygen circulating to all your tissues!

💪 Healthy Living:
* Enjoy deeper sleep and relaxation like never before.
* Slow down the aging process and stay forever young. 
* Increase your endurance with more mitochondria in your muscles.
* Boost your alkaline reserve for those emergency situations.
* Supercharge your immune system and fend off pesky colds and allergies.
* Lower blood pressure and restore balance after intense activity.

In the art of life, sometimes the wisest move is to retreat!  
It's not surrender, but a strategic withdrawal to gather strength, rest without guilt, recalibrate, and of course emerge with greater clarity and purpose. 

This past month I embraced the fresh approach real estate retreat with arms wide open. Amidst the breathtaking landscapes of the retreat, we delved into discussions that transcended the ordinary. Change was not just a topic; it was a ripple of freedom, and growth echoed the sentiment that time is most valuable currency we have.🍃

Leadership conversations throughout the retreat became a guide to steering not just our businesses but also our lives. As we unfolded life and business goals, the air became super charged with the essence of limitless possibilities.

In the golden hues of the setting sun, we contemplated the win-win mentality, realizing that true freedom also lies in collaborative success. Throughout the many games and events, we learned that working together doesn't diminish individuality; instead, it enhances the tapestry of achievements.

Yoga sessions weren't just about physical rejuvenation, although that was definitely needed haha; they were a portal to mental clarity and the freedom to breathe in the new perspectives. Breath work became a metaphor for me releasing the old, creating space for the new, aligning our energies with the goals we set for ourselves over the weekend. 
In all of these moments, I realized that the true beauty of our journey lies in the freedom we have to choose our path daily and consciously create our destiny. Madeleine L'Engle one of my favourite authors who wrote “A Wrinkle in Time” says so perfectly, “we can't take any credit for our talents. It's how we use them that counts.” 

Wishing for everyone reading this post that your visions continue to evolve, your goals turn into achievements, and all of our journeys be as rich and fulfilling as the discussions that were shared under the sun-kissed sky during this retreat.
